"Notwithstanding all the high encomiums and mn- tual gratulations which they give one another, (for I am far from censuring the whole of that illus- trious society, to which the learned world is much obliged) after all those golden dreams at the Louvre, that their pieces will be as much valued, ten or twelve ages hence, as the ancient Greek or Roman, 3 can no more get it into my head that they will Jast so long, than I could believe the learned Dr. H k 3, of the Royal Society, if he should pre- tend to show me a butterfly that had lived a thou- sand winters."